inputs.description: A collection of arguments for invoking getAccountPublicAccessBlock.

accountId.description: AWS account ID to configure. Defaults to automatically determined account ID of the AWS provider.

outputs.description: A collection of values returned by getAccountPublicAccessBlock.

blockPublicAcls.description: Whether or not Amazon S3 should block public ACLs for buckets in this account is enabled. Returns as `true` or `false`.

blockPublicPolicy.description: Whether or not Amazon S3 should block public bucket policies for buckets in this account is enabled. Returns as `true` or `false`.

id.description: The provider-assigned unique ID for this managed resource.

ignorePublicAcls.description: Whether or not Amazon S3 should ignore public ACLs for buckets in this account is enabled. Returns as `true` or `false`.

restrictPublicBuckets.description: Whether or not Amazon S3 should restrict public bucket policies for buckets in this account is enabled. Returns as `true` or `false`.
